description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;There is a fantastic opportunity to join the Ward 2 leadership team.&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There is an opportunity for a band 6 junior sister/charge nurse for ward 2 and elective Orthopaedic ward at the Royal Orthopaedic Hospital, if you believe you have all the skills to join the band 6 team, then please apply!&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Why come and work on Ward 2?&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ward 2 is a 24 bedded inpatient unit providing orthopaedic large joint services to adult patients. The Royal Orthopaedic Hospital is an internationally recognised Centre of Excellence for the diagnosis and treatment of a variety of orthopaedic conditions. The large joint ‘rapid recovery’ pathway, based on ward 2. As a trust, we are at the cutting edge of advancements in orthopaedic surgery and research. We also provide a Bone Infection Unit (BIU) service and Ward 2 provides nursing care for patients being treated under this service.&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a nursing team, we have made vast improvements to develop our nursing processes to ensure that we provide the best in nursing care to our patients. We pride ourselves in ensuring that we consistently challenge ourselves to provide the best care to our patients to ensure they are able to recover from their operation and return home with an improved quality of life.&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;On Ward 2 the focus of nursing and physiotherapy care is streamlining pathways and process and ensuring that patients receive the best joint replacement care possible. This is in connection with the Stryker Company based in America and the Royal Orthopaedic Hospital is be a leading force in the UK as we will be the first hospital in the country to move towards this new way of working.&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you would like to work on a ward that values you, supports you in allowing you the time to really care and is committed to your professional development then apply today! &lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Informal visits prior to application or interview are welcome.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information, please contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Erin Baldwin, Senior Sister on 0121 685 4090&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
